The paper proposes a method for calibrating LiDAR and camera systems, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves using visual reconstruction of the environment, which is a machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) technique. The paper also discusses the influence of different placements of chessboards, which is related to system identification and control (cs.SY).
